# App datatable integration

## Required endpoints per table

1. **Columns** — `Get*Columns` → `datatable.GetColumns(columns)`
2. **List API** — parse query, query DB, return `data` + `pagination`
3. **List view** (optional) — same data shape for SSR

## Standard list handler

```go
columns, err := cc.getFooColumns(ctx)
q, err := tablequery.Extract(c, columns)
items, pagination, err := postgresql.FindRaw[map[string]any](db, q, columns, tableName).Run()
datatable.FormatContent(&items, columns)
return c.JSON(fiber.Map{
    "data": items,
    "pagination": datatable.RenderPagination(pagination),
})
```

Use `postgresql.Find[Model](db.Model(&Model{}), q, columns)` for simple GORM models without custom SELECT.

Use `FindRaw` when `SQLColumn` has expressions, subqueries, or `.AddJoin(...)`.

## Column definition checklist

- Stable `ID` (matches frontend filter/sort state)
- `AccessorKey` usually equals `ID` (camelCase in JSON rows)
- `SQLColumn` for anything not a plain column name
- `FilterSQLColumn` when UI shows labels but filters store ids
- `Meta.Variant`: `text`, `number`, `date`, `select`, `multiSelect`, `boolean`, etc.
- `Meta.Options` for select/multiSelect (load from DB in `get*Columns`)
- `Meta.FilterBy` for dependent dropdowns (refetch columns when parent filter changes)
- `Hidden: true` for id / internal columns still needed in SQL
- `EnableOnlyAdvancedFilters: true` to hide from simple toolbar only

## Dependent filter options

When `Meta.FilterBy` is set, read parent value in `get*Columns`:

```go
studyLevel := tablequery.GetFilterValue(c, "study_level")
// rebuild Meta.Options for faculty column
```

## Custom stats / non-table filters

Use `tablequery.GetFilter` / `GetFilterValue` for one-off query params without adding a column.

## Imports

```go
"github.com/flowtrove/packages/datatable"
"github.com/flowtrove/packages/datatable/postgresql"
"github.com/uetedu/app/pkg/tablequery"
```

## Response contract

- `pagination`: `{ page, limit, total, total_pages, pageCount }`
- Row keys must match `AccessorKey` (or `ID`) from columns

